holograms @Nov 28, 2025


Taiga		Rated:

Its long, very long. 8 hours and 20 minutes does not pass easily.

The sheer length gives Ulrike Ottinger the rare gift of not having to cut as much. She lets scenes expand as long as they naturally go on for. The length itself is also very impressive, it feels like a grand achievement just having watched this.

I'm thinking a lot about the question that Jean Rouch/Edgar Morin posed in Chronique d'un t (Paris 1960) [Chronicle of a Summer]: how to get to the truth in documentary filmmaking? Ottinger focuses on peo...

aquatheology
11/27 23:31 CETDST
Thank you for suggesting D'Est! I've kind of skipped over it while browsing your 5*, mostly because my (only) brief encounter with Chantal Ackerman was Jeanne Dielmann, like for many people, I guess, and I did not love it.

For me, Children of Paradise holds a special place also considering the circumstances of its creation (mostly under Nazi occupation) as an act of creative resistance... but also because I have ADORED its scope, sheer ambition and, well, the melodrama as well. :) But I can see that this doesn't hit the same way if you don't connect with it particularly.

Taiga is on my watchlist as well, although I think that both movies are actually quite different. Chamisso's Shadow has heavy voice-over, mostly from the diaries of Ottinger & the first explorers of the Bering Strait as well as Adalbert von Chamisso himself, so if often feels like an essay movie more than an ethnographic movie - from what I've seen of Taiga, there is far less talking in that one, but I might be wrong.

Fair enough. Kan mjligtvis ha en lgre standard fr kortfilmer men jag gillade stmningen mellan grabbarna. Kan inte identifiera mig s mycket med supporterkulturen men hela grejen med att hamna i fel sllskap tyckte jag funkade bra, och scenen dr den ene stod och blev ignorerad av de tv andra var ju klockren observationshumor :) tyckte vningskrningsscenen gav nn sorts eftertryck ocks.

Underbara synpunkter gllande Play, tack fr dem! Hehe jo, jag r vl lite geners - det ger ju mer tyngd att ha s f hga betyg som du (som du fr vrigt har valt med omsorg, lskar de flesta som jag sett bland niorna och tiorna!) - men ven bland mina rtt frikostiga nior tillhr Play toppen. lskar Haneke och Den sjunde kontinenten, vilket r en rimlig jmfrelse ven om stlund kanske har lite mer humor och lite mindre svrta. Han r nog mer Haneke light n Roy Andersson light (som jag ofta lser) i varje fall, frn vad jag har sett.

Jo, mycket knns igen frn De ofrivilliga som jag ocks lskade. Dels tematiskt med alla olika maktfrhllandena (vuxna mot barn, invandrare mot svenskar, starkare mot svagare, fler mot frre och kanske kvinnor mot mn i scenen du nmnde (tror inte det var en slump i alla fall)). De r ju rtt lika ven stilistiskt, gillar verkligen hans stt att lta mycket ske utanfr kameran, vilket fr mig speglar nt slags ansiktslshet hos frvarna. Indianerna strde mig inte s mycket (tyckte sista scenen som jag har fr mig anspelade p dem var rtt fin), men fattar inte heller var bajsandet kom ifrn.

Tack fr rekommendationen! Ska frska se den andra stlundfilmen :)
